%% Flow: incoming Telegram message routing
%% Last updated: 2026-07-12
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Andrii
    participant TG as Telegram API
    participant TW as telegram_watcher.py
    participant CD as command_dispatcher.py
    participant C as claude -p (conv)
    participant IB as inbox/pending.json
    participant W as Execution Session

    U->>TG: sends message
    TW->>TG: getUpdates (long-poll)
    TG-->>TW: message

    alt starts with /
        TW->>CD: dispatch command
        CD-->>TW: response text
        TW->>TG: sendMessage (reply)
    else chat message
        TW->>C: pass to conversational agent
        C->>C: generate response
        C-->>TW: response text
        TW->>TG: sendMessage (reply)

        alt task_request or idea
            C->>IB: inbox_append.py (write pending.json)
            Note over IB,W: Next execution session reads inbox_startup.py
            W->>IB: inbox_startup.py → creates Loom task
        end
    end
